HEADWORD: Untuck
<hw>Un*tuck"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>tuck</ets>.]</ety> <def>To unfold or undo, as a
tuck; to release from a tuck or fold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

